===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|pigmentum||pigment|lang=la}}, itself from {{term/t|la|pingō||I paint}} + {{term|-mentum|lang=la}}; variants of this word may have been known in Old English (e.g. 12th century [[pyhmentum]]).

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|biology|lang=en}} Any [[color]] in [[plant]] or [[animal]] [[cell]]s
#: ''Chlorophyll is the '''pigment''' responsible for most plants' green colouring.''
# A dry [[colorant]], usually an insoluble powder
#: ''[[umber|Umber]] is a '''pigment''' made from clay containing iron and manganese oxide.''
# {{context|obsolete|lang=en}} [[wine|Wine]] flavoured with [[spice]]s and [[honey]].
#: {{rfquotek|Sir Walter Scott}}

